cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on solving the stochastic reachability problem in multi-agent systems using an adaptive neighborhood algorithm. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper presents a model-predictive control algorithm for each agent and a cost-based Lyapunov function for adaptive resizing of the neighborhood. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses statistical model checking to evaluate the performance of the algorithm. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper uses a consensus-based approach to derive the flock-wide optimal solution. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the benefits of the algorithm for any controllable multi-agent system, which could include robotic systems.
